[The latest total numbers of lab-confirmed SBV-affected animal holdings in the 8 countries are:
cattle - 406 (see comment)
sheep - 1991
goats - 59
total - 2456

The actual number of affected cattle holdings is assumed to be much higher, since animals seem to have tested PCR-negative more than 5 months post infection (infected during early pregnancy). This is supported by the results of a Dutch serosurvey (see archived posting 20120309.1065831) and reflected by the number of cattle farms which have submitted complaints on malformed calves. In Netherlands (506) and Belgium (357) combined, 863 complaining cattle holdings have tested negative. The number of SBV-positive cattle farms among the submissions has been increasing since late February 2012, while the appearance of malformed lambs is reaching its terminal stage. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1zJl.]
